1
00:02:49,760 --> 00:02:53,000
Are you telling me you love my daughter?

2
00:02:59,120 --> 00:02:59,960
You shameless woman!

3
00:03:09,680 --> 00:03:14,040
<i>I have another job for you.
Easy work, quick pay. Interested?</i>

4
00:03:33,080 --> 00:03:34,200
Ms. Pakarang.

5
00:03:35,840 --> 00:03:37,240
Is something wrong?

6
00:03:46,520 --> 00:03:49,240
No, I'm fine.

7
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:54,800
It's cold. I'll go outside first.

8
00:04:16,440 --> 00:04:18,319
Good morning, Ms. Sairung.

9
00:04:18,320 --> 00:04:20,679
You got here so early today.

10
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:24,119
Why is Mr. Phum calling an urgent meeting?
Why wasn't I informed?

11
00:04:24,120 --> 00:04:27,400
I hear it's about
the photography exhibition.

12
00:04:28,720 --> 00:04:29,920
Kaimook's photos.

13
00:04:30,880 --> 00:04:32,120
Is she here?

14
00:04:35,360 --> 00:04:37,839
Oh, yes.

15
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:40,680
I saw Mr. Phum bring a woman with him.

16
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:43,679
Thanks for keeping an eye
on things for me.

17
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:46,599
You'll get a special bonus at the end
of the year. Now get back to work.

18
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:48,920
Thank you, Ms. Sairung.

19
00:04:57,680 --> 00:04:59,439
Before we begin today's meeting,

20
00:04:59,440 --> 00:05:01,399
I'd like to introduce a new member

21
00:05:01,400 --> 00:05:04,159
of our company to all of you.

22
00:05:04,160 --> 00:05:05,480
This is Ms. Pakarang.

23
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,959
She'll be Ms. Su's assistant.

24
00:05:09,960 --> 00:05:12,679
She'll be coordinating

25
00:05:12,680 --> 00:05:14,879
our upcoming photography exhibition,

26
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:19,519
which will raise funds
for a coral restoration project.

27
00:05:19,520 --> 00:05:21,359
Some of you may be surprised

28
00:05:21,360 --> 00:05:24,479
that I've decided to launch this project.

29
00:05:24,480 --> 00:05:25,999
I believe it's time

30
00:05:26,000 --> 00:05:30,279
for all of us
to help address environmental issues.

31
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:31,439
These problems are important,

32
00:05:31,440 --> 00:05:33,880
yet they've been neglected
for far too long.

33
00:05:34,880 --> 00:05:38,759
This exhibition will help people

34
00:05:38,760 --> 00:05:42,319
see the importance and beauty of the sea,

35
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:43,679
especially the coral reef.

36
00:05:43,680 --> 00:05:47,479
They have been destroyed
at an alarming rate.

37
00:05:47,480 --> 00:05:51,919
I want us and everyone in this company

38
00:05:51,920 --> 00:05:54,199
to take part in this project.

39
00:05:54,200 --> 00:05:57,000
Please coordinate, everyone.

40
00:06:00,120 --> 00:06:02,000
That's an excellent idea, sir.

41
00:06:02,840 --> 00:06:05,520
It's one of the best ways
to give back to society.

42
00:06:11,680 --> 00:06:15,160
The details are in the documents
you all have right now.

43
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:17,200
PHOTOGRAPHY EXHIBITION

44
00:06:26,600 --> 00:06:29,920
Take a seat, Sairung.
I'll continue the meeting.

45
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:31,240
‎Uh...

46
00:06:33,080 --> 00:06:37,039
Oh, Ms. Sairung,
please have a seat right here.

47
00:06:37,040 --> 00:06:41,560
I was about to take photos of the meeting.

48
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,959
Alright.

49
00:06:44,960 --> 00:06:48,039
For the details of the exhibition,

50
00:06:48,040 --> 00:06:49,400
- I want everyone to--
- Hold on.

51
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:53,640
As Mr. Phum's wife,

52
00:06:54,480 --> 00:06:56,960
I haven't even been introduced
to this new employee.

53
00:06:57,560 --> 00:07:00,800
What position will you be holding?

54
00:07:03,680 --> 00:07:06,600
This is Ms. Pakarang.
She will be assisting Ms. Su.

55
00:07:10,360 --> 00:07:13,120
You put her in my old position, Mr. Phum?

56
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:19,200
Alright.

57
00:07:20,120 --> 00:07:24,119
This exhibition
will feature a lot of photos.

58
00:07:24,120 --> 00:07:28,640
- I'll show you what we'll have.
- Alright. I'll handle it.

59
00:07:30,520 --> 00:07:32,200
Ms. Pakarang,

60
00:07:32,960 --> 00:07:34,880
won't you help Ms. Su?

61
00:07:39,840 --> 00:07:41,480
Here, sir.

62
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:44,600
You can show everyone the photos.

63
00:08:08,320 --> 00:08:10,080
I don't know how to use it.

64
00:08:12,840 --> 00:08:16,039
This is your secretary's assistant?

65
00:08:16,040 --> 00:08:18,079
I think she'd be better off

66
00:08:18,080 --> 00:08:21,200
helping the housekeepers serve tea
and coffee during meetings.

67
00:08:22,240 --> 00:08:23,640
It's alright.

68
00:08:25,240 --> 00:08:26,960
- Ms. Su.
- I'll do it.

69
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:34,440
Let's see the first photo.

70
00:08:36,440 --> 00:08:37,799
PHOTOGRAPHY EXHIBITION

71
00:08:48,520 --> 00:08:52,079
They're beautiful.
Do these corals have names?

72
00:08:52,080 --> 00:08:53,480
Yes,

73
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:56,039
but I can't remember them all.

74
00:08:56,040 --> 00:08:58,759
But it's fine.
We'll put their name on every photo.

75
00:08:58,760 --> 00:08:59,960
Yes.

76
00:09:00,560 --> 00:09:02,360
It's Cauliflower coral.

77
00:09:09,480 --> 00:09:12,600
Then let's see the second photo.

78
00:09:18,920 --> 00:09:21,600
That's Staghorn coral.

79
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:31,880
Let's move on to the third one.

80
00:09:34,880 --> 00:09:36,520
Branching Pore coral.

81
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:51,840
I really don't know
how I said all of that.

82
00:09:53,360 --> 00:09:57,520
Maybe it's part of a memory
you once had.

83
00:10:04,840 --> 00:10:07,519
I've prepared a desk for you,
Ms. Pakarang.

84
00:10:07,520 --> 00:10:09,999
If there's anything you don't understand,
feel free to ask me anytime.

85
00:10:10,000 --> 00:10:11,240
Thank you.

86
00:10:12,440 --> 00:10:14,040
I'll excuse myself.

87
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,280
Please.

88
00:10:25,120 --> 00:10:26,520
Here are the photos.

89
00:10:31,480 --> 00:10:32,599
Her face is clearly visible.

90
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:36,239
Please send these
to the investigator I contacted.

91
00:10:36,240 --> 00:10:37,599
Yes, Mr. Phum.

92
00:10:37,600 --> 00:10:39,639
Tell them to treat it as urgent.

93
00:10:39,640 --> 00:10:42,800
Ms. Pakarang should be reunited
with her family as soon as possible.

94
00:10:43,560 --> 00:10:44,639
Understood.

95
00:10:44,640 --> 00:10:45,880
Excuse me then.

96
00:11:09,040 --> 00:11:10,680
I'm happy for you, Mook.

97
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:15,120
Oh.

98
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:22,839
So Mr. Narathon really knows
that woman ghost, right?

99
00:11:22,840 --> 00:11:24,599
Who is she?

100
00:11:24,600 --> 00:11:28,360
Why did she die?
And why has she been following me?

101
00:11:29,400 --> 00:11:32,920
She was an old friend of Mr. Narathon's.

102
00:11:34,720 --> 00:11:35,960
A friend?

103
00:11:36,560 --> 00:11:37,520
Yes.

104
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:42,640
But as to why she died
and why she's following you,

105
00:11:43,160 --> 00:11:45,920
Mr. Narathon wants to know that too.

106
00:11:50,320 --> 00:11:54,479
Actually, Da, try thinking back.

107
00:11:54,480 --> 00:11:58,279
When was the first time
that ghost contacted you?

108
00:11:58,280 --> 00:12:02,000
Where was it? And what did she say?

109
00:12:04,960 --> 00:12:06,000
Hold on.

110
00:12:06,920 --> 00:12:08,920
The first time?

111
00:12:19,040 --> 00:12:21,920
What?! What is this?

112
00:12:36,680 --> 00:12:39,359
The first time I saw that ghost

113
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:41,000
was at your beach house.

114
00:12:43,360 --> 00:12:45,599
The beach house?

115
00:12:45,600 --> 00:12:47,039
Yeah.

116
00:12:47,040 --> 00:12:51,240
As for what she said, I can't remember.
I was too scared back then.

117
00:13:25,760 --> 00:13:29,520
It's not time for him to know

118
00:13:31,760 --> 00:13:33,120
who you are.

119
00:14:25,720 --> 00:14:27,840
Mr. Mek's beach house?

120
00:14:29,280 --> 00:14:30,200
Yes.

121
00:14:30,840 --> 00:14:33,160
I think that place must have
something to do with Sarai.

122
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:37,760
Sarai first contacted Da at that house,

123
00:14:39,200 --> 00:14:43,280
then kept following Da
all the way to the condo and Skull Island.

124
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:48,159
That's right.

125
00:14:48,160 --> 00:14:51,120
Sarai once told me
her house was by the sea,

126
00:14:52,480 --> 00:14:55,680
but I never asked where.

127
00:14:57,920 --> 00:15:00,039
I'll try asking my dad

128
00:15:00,040 --> 00:15:02,040
who the original owner of the house was.

129
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:07,200
If it really was Sarai, it'll be easier
for us to investigate her story.

130
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:16,640
Is something wrong?

131
00:15:19,840 --> 00:15:20,840
I just find it strange.

132
00:15:22,880 --> 00:15:24,720
Ever since we came back from Skull Island,

133
00:15:25,520 --> 00:15:27,560
Sarai's spirit has gone completely silent.

134
00:15:29,200 --> 00:15:31,640
She hasn't appeared to Ms. Da again.

135
00:15:33,160 --> 00:15:34,360
That's true.

136
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:38,360
Where did her spirit go?

137
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:02,640
Oh.

138
00:16:03,720 --> 00:16:05,879
Did you go to the restroom?

139
00:16:05,880 --> 00:16:07,279
Yes.

140
00:16:07,280 --> 00:16:10,959
This is your desk I've prepared.

141
00:16:10,960 --> 00:16:12,559
I'm sitting right here.

142
00:16:12,560 --> 00:16:15,799
If there's something you don't understand,
you can always ask me.

143
00:16:15,800 --> 00:16:17,040
Thank you.

144
00:16:26,640 --> 00:16:27,880
Well,

145
00:16:28,480 --> 00:16:30,999
if you're hungry
or want something to drink,

146
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:33,119
walk out to the right.

147
00:16:33,120 --> 00:16:36,520
There's a pantry there.
You can help yourself.

148
00:16:37,280 --> 00:16:39,879
Thank you, but I'm not hungry at all.

149
00:16:39,880 --> 00:16:41,320
Alright.

150
00:16:46,320 --> 00:16:47,720
Or do I need to eat something?

151
00:16:50,080 --> 00:16:50,960
Yes?

152
00:16:52,400 --> 00:16:54,119
Nothing.

153
00:16:54,120 --> 00:16:58,039
I'm going out to meet a client.

154
00:16:58,040 --> 00:16:59,839
If Mr. Phum calls,

155
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:02,839
please fill in for me. Alright?

156
00:17:02,840 --> 00:17:03,880
- Okay.
- I'll get going now.

157
00:17:14,640 --> 00:17:17,319
Are you thinking about your next scheme?

158
00:17:21,680 --> 00:17:25,358
Impressive. Besides working in bed,

159
00:17:25,359 --> 00:17:27,680
you've managed
to climb your way into the company.

160
00:17:29,120 --> 00:17:32,440
But don't think you'll get past me.

161
00:17:38,360 --> 00:17:39,880
You dare walk away from me?

162
00:17:53,920 --> 00:17:55,000
Sairung!

163
00:17:55,880 --> 00:17:57,439
What the hell are you doing now?

164
00:17:57,440 --> 00:17:59,199
This is a workplace.

165
00:17:59,200 --> 00:18:02,319
I... I haven't done anything.

166
00:18:02,320 --> 00:18:04,240
Pakarang, are you alright?

167
00:18:05,640 --> 00:18:06,720
Are you alright?

168
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:08,919
Leave now.

169
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:12,080
If you don't leave,
I'll have security drag you out.

170
00:18:12,680 --> 00:18:13,759
‎Go get some rest.

171
00:18:13,760 --> 00:18:15,279
Mr. Phum,

172
00:18:15,280 --> 00:18:16,560
I...

173
00:18:17,360 --> 00:18:18,440
Mr. Phum.

174
00:18:24,400 --> 00:18:28,000
You two-faced little snake.
I didn't even do anything to you.

175
00:18:30,360 --> 00:18:31,840
I won't let you get away with this.

176
00:18:42,720 --> 00:18:43,920
How are you feeling?

177
00:18:46,520 --> 00:18:49,360
I just feel so weak.

178
00:18:51,000 --> 00:18:52,919
You must have been so startled
you almost fainted.

179
00:18:52,920 --> 00:18:55,519
I'll ask the maid
to make you some herbal tonic.

180
00:18:55,520 --> 00:18:57,040
Wait here.

181
00:19:02,840 --> 00:19:03,960
How clumsy.

182
00:19:26,440 --> 00:19:27,560
Blood.

183
00:19:28,160 --> 00:19:29,680
It's alright. Just a small cut.

184
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:01,639
You can't stop bleeding like that.

185
00:20:01,640 --> 00:20:05,080
My hand is dirty. You could get infected.

186
00:20:07,720 --> 00:20:09,520
I'm sorry.

187
00:20:10,280 --> 00:20:11,280
Well,

188
00:20:12,760 --> 00:20:13,920
I...

189
00:20:16,160 --> 00:20:18,960
I was so worried about you
that I forgot myself.

190
00:20:23,560 --> 00:20:24,840
Pakarang.

191
00:20:27,320 --> 00:20:29,559
Just sit and rest first.

192
00:20:29,560 --> 00:20:30,640
Come on.

193
00:20:32,960 --> 00:20:34,800
I'll go get your medicine.

194
00:21:23,760 --> 00:21:27,400
Now I know how to preserve your body.

195
00:22:25,600 --> 00:22:27,040
Son.

196
00:22:28,800 --> 00:22:30,440
This isn't human blood!

197
00:22:31,240 --> 00:22:32,720
What is this?

198
00:22:33,760 --> 00:22:34,800
Well.

199
00:22:35,400 --> 00:22:38,600
Our island has been sealed off.
No one comes here anymore.

200
00:22:39,280 --> 00:22:41,240
I had to bring you animal blood for now.

201
00:22:49,640 --> 00:22:51,720
I need human blood.

202
00:22:52,600 --> 00:22:56,080
Only human blood can restore my body.

203
00:23:30,440 --> 00:23:33,280
<i>I was so worried about you
that I forgot myself.</i>

204
00:23:52,920 --> 00:23:54,720
I need to talk to you.

205
00:23:55,400 --> 00:23:57,719
You're being fooled by Pakarang.

206
00:23:57,720 --> 00:23:58,920
What else are you going to say?

207
00:23:59,760 --> 00:24:02,000
What you did today was bad enough.

208
00:24:05,160 --> 00:24:07,239
I didn't do anything to Pakarang.

209
00:24:07,240 --> 00:24:11,240
But you took her side so completely
you don't even see me anymore.

210
00:24:12,480 --> 00:24:15,199
You yanked out a clump of her hair
and insulted her until she fainted.

211
00:24:15,200 --> 00:24:16,720
And you still say you didn't do anything?

212
00:24:17,320 --> 00:24:18,400
She was acting to fool you.

213
00:24:18,920 --> 00:24:22,759
A two-faced woman like that,
if you keep her close, you'll regret it.

214
00:24:22,760 --> 00:24:24,960
I believe what I see.

215
00:24:30,040 --> 00:24:31,600
You believe what you see?

216
00:24:33,120 --> 00:24:36,440
It's because you're this stupid
that you lost Sarai.

217
00:27:30,240 --> 00:27:31,320
You evil bitch.

218
00:27:32,560 --> 00:27:33,840
You deserve to die.

219
00:27:36,760 --> 00:27:41,000
KITKARNWATTANA FURNITURE

220
00:27:58,280 --> 00:28:01,519
Mom, where have you been?

221
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:05,520
My girl, why did you come out?

222
00:28:06,120 --> 00:28:08,599
- I'm hungry.
- Oh, my girl.

223
00:28:08,600 --> 00:28:10,480
Let's go.

224
00:29:22,680 --> 00:29:24,600
Killing someone

225
00:29:27,400 --> 00:29:29,080
isn't easy.

226
00:29:39,560 --> 00:29:40,760
So why?

227
00:29:42,720 --> 00:29:45,160
Why was it so easy for you to kill me?

228
00:29:47,440 --> 00:29:49,320
Why were you so cold-blooded,

229
00:29:51,240 --> 00:29:52,520
Mr. Phum?

230
00:30:57,040 --> 00:30:59,880
No!

231
00:31:03,400 --> 00:31:04,959
Were you dreaming about Sarai?

232
00:31:04,960 --> 00:31:06,720
You called her name loud enough.

233
00:31:18,160 --> 00:31:21,359
Her spirit must be jealous
seeing you with a new woman.

234
00:31:21,360 --> 00:31:22,560
That's why she's haunting your dreams.

235
00:31:30,520 --> 00:31:33,000
How do you know
I dreamed of Sarai as a ghost?

236
00:31:39,480 --> 00:31:42,839
Well, you shouted so loudly

237
00:31:42,840 --> 00:31:44,399
like you were terrified.

238
00:31:44,400 --> 00:31:46,080
I'd assume she appeared as a ghost.

239
00:31:48,520 --> 00:31:50,800
I'm going back to sleep.

240
00:32:17,920 --> 00:32:22,639
I think humans are the biggest
destroyers of ecosystems.

241
00:32:22,640 --> 00:32:23,760
Don't you think so?

242
00:32:25,280 --> 00:32:28,279
Oh, don't talk academics with me.

243
00:32:28,280 --> 00:32:30,839
Goodness, I just found out

244
00:32:30,840 --> 00:32:34,439
this facial cream contains radish extract.

245
00:32:34,440 --> 00:32:35,360
Wow.

246
00:32:37,520 --> 00:32:39,760
You can make skincare products
from radishes, Mom?

247
00:32:40,360 --> 00:32:41,559
Exactly.

248
00:32:41,560 --> 00:32:43,919
I just learned radishes

249
00:32:43,920 --> 00:32:46,720
can help fade freckles and dark spots.

250
00:32:47,320 --> 00:32:48,239
Hey.

251
00:32:48,240 --> 00:32:50,479
And now all these rich people

252
00:32:50,480 --> 00:32:53,399
keep buying up beachfront land
to build resorts.

253
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:55,879
If there's no proper management,

254
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:58,320
it's bound to cause damage eventually.

255
00:33:00,600 --> 00:33:03,919
Is that why you refused
to sell our land to Mr. Phum?

256
00:33:03,920 --> 00:33:06,599
Exactly.

257
00:33:06,600 --> 00:33:10,599
Just looking at him, you can tell
he's a natural-born destroyer of nature.

258
00:33:10,600 --> 00:33:12,199
Well.

259
00:33:12,200 --> 00:33:15,439
You're being unfair to him.

260
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:17,559
He looks quite handsome

261
00:33:17,560 --> 00:33:19,320
and much younger than you.

262
00:33:25,840 --> 00:33:30,040
By the way,
who owned our beach house before us?

263
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:33,560
I think her name was

264
00:33:34,120 --> 00:33:36,120
Ms. Boonsong.

265
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:38,240
Boonsong?

266
00:33:43,760 --> 00:33:46,160
Do you know where she lives?

267
00:33:46,960 --> 00:33:49,119
I don't remember clearly.

268
00:33:49,120 --> 00:33:51,119
Somewhere behind the temple.

269
00:33:51,120 --> 00:33:54,560
But actually,
the land didn't belonged to her.

270
00:33:56,440 --> 00:33:58,159
What do you mean?

271
00:33:58,160 --> 00:34:02,199
The original owner
was in financial trouble

272
00:34:02,200 --> 00:34:04,599
and mortgaged the land.

273
00:34:04,600 --> 00:34:07,159
Eventually, they defaulted.

274
00:34:07,160 --> 00:34:09,718
Ms. Boonsong put it up for sale,
and I bought it

275
00:34:09,719 --> 00:34:12,920
to build our house. Why are you asking?

276
00:34:13,520 --> 00:34:15,480
Oh, no reason. Just curious.

277
00:34:16,920 --> 00:34:20,158
Um, I'm heading out.
I'll probably be home late,

278
00:34:20,159 --> 00:34:22,479
so don't wait for me for dinner.

279
00:34:22,480 --> 00:34:24,159
Going out with Da?

280
00:34:24,760 --> 00:34:25,760
Yes.

281
00:34:27,080 --> 00:34:28,400
I'll go now.

282
00:34:37,199 --> 00:34:40,600
Everyone will like it.

283
00:35:02,440 --> 00:35:03,759
Hello, Ms. Pakarang.

284
00:35:03,760 --> 00:35:07,439
I'd like to ask you
to have breakfast downstairs.

285
00:35:07,440 --> 00:35:08,920
Would you be interested?

286
00:35:18,960 --> 00:35:20,920
Thank you for inviting me.

287
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:24,400
But I'm not feeling very well.
Please, go ahead.

288
00:35:25,800 --> 00:35:27,159
No wonder.

289
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:31,159
I was wondering why you look so pale.

290
00:35:31,160 --> 00:35:32,920
There's no color in your face at all.

291
00:35:40,840 --> 00:35:44,240
What's that smell? Can you smell that?

292
00:35:44,920 --> 00:35:48,200
It smells like something rotting.

293
00:35:52,400 --> 00:35:56,280
Maybe it's coming from over there.

294
00:36:03,000 --> 00:36:05,879
How awful. They're working so carelessly.

295
00:36:05,880 --> 00:36:07,880
I should probably complain to Mr. Phum.

296
00:36:11,320 --> 00:36:13,760
Well then, I'll be going.

297
00:36:14,320 --> 00:36:15,480
- Okay.
- Bye.

298
00:36:29,960 --> 00:36:31,719
Oh?

299
00:36:31,720 --> 00:36:34,680
Why doesn't it smell here at all?

300
00:37:58,680 --> 00:38:00,200
Hello, Mr. Phum.

301
00:38:05,080 --> 00:38:07,200
How did you know it was me?

302
00:38:14,280 --> 00:38:18,359
Who else
would be calling me here besides you?

303
00:38:18,360 --> 00:38:20,679
That's true.

304
00:38:20,680 --> 00:38:22,279
Are you ready yet?

305
00:38:22,280 --> 00:38:24,520
I can pick you up
and we can go to the office together.

306
00:38:25,920 --> 00:38:27,920
I'd like to take a day off.

307
00:38:29,760 --> 00:38:31,319
<i>You're still not feeling better?</i>

308
00:38:31,320 --> 00:38:33,759
Is it serious?

309
00:38:33,760 --> 00:38:35,079
Should I take you to see a doctor?

310
00:38:35,080 --> 00:38:36,680
That's not necessary.

311
00:38:38,080 --> 00:38:40,160
I just feel a little weak.

312
00:38:40,800 --> 00:38:43,080
If I get some rest, I'll be fine.

313
00:38:45,440 --> 00:38:47,199
Don't worry about me.

314
00:38:47,200 --> 00:38:49,120
I can take care of myself.

315
00:38:50,360 --> 00:38:53,119
If you change your mind and want to
see a doctor, call me.

316
00:38:53,120 --> 00:38:54,600
I'll go with you.

317
00:38:55,640 --> 00:38:56,720
Thank you.

318
00:39:30,080 --> 00:39:32,759
I don't think it'll be difficult
to find Ms. Boonsong's house.

319
00:39:32,760 --> 00:39:34,959
Dad said it was somewhere
behind the temple.

320
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:35,880
Yeah.

321
00:39:36,480 --> 00:39:39,160
I think we're getting closer to the truth.

322
00:39:41,200 --> 00:39:42,640
Thank you so much, Kaimook.

323
00:39:44,720 --> 00:39:46,039
Without you,

324
00:39:46,040 --> 00:39:48,520
I couldn't have gotten this far.

325
00:39:49,320 --> 00:39:51,080
I promised I'd help you.

326
00:39:51,680 --> 00:39:53,120
So I have to see it through.

327
00:39:58,640 --> 00:40:00,200
JASMINE RICE AND ALL TYPES OF RICE

328
00:41:01,960 --> 00:41:02,800
What would you like?

329
00:41:10,320 --> 00:41:11,400
I'd like to buy blood.

330
00:41:32,760 --> 00:41:35,599
Here. It must be this house.

331
00:41:35,600 --> 00:41:38,839
BOONSONG HOUSE

332
00:41:38,840 --> 00:41:40,040
Excuse me.

333
00:41:41,440 --> 00:41:42,800
Is anyone home?

334
00:41:45,400 --> 00:41:46,600
Is anyone home?

335
00:41:50,400 --> 00:41:52,600
Who are you looking for?

336
00:41:53,920 --> 00:41:55,319
Is Aunt Boonsong home?

337
00:41:55,320 --> 00:41:58,799
No. She went to Bangkok yesterday
and will probably be back this afternoon.

338
00:41:58,800 --> 00:42:01,680
Do the two of you need something?

339
00:43:49,280 --> 00:43:50,760
Why is this happening?

340
00:44:03,720 --> 00:44:05,079
I'm worried about you.

341
00:44:05,080 --> 00:44:07,519
<i>What about me?
Were you ever worried about me?</i>

342
00:44:07,520 --> 00:44:09,639
Did you ever miss me?

343
00:44:09,640 --> 00:44:10,719
Hello.

344
00:44:10,720 --> 00:44:11,800
Mr. Narathon.

345
00:44:13,440 --> 00:44:14,359
Who are you really?

346
00:44:14,360 --> 00:44:18,240
I think the way she acts
and speaks is exactly like...

347
00:44:19,080 --> 00:44:20,080
Like who?

348
00:44:20,920 --> 00:44:22,160
Sarai.

349
00:44:51,760 --> 00:44:54,000
Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
